{{Politics of Qatar}}
A '''referendum to approve a new constitution''' was held in [[Qatar]] on 29 April 2003. The constitution was overwhelmingly approved, with almost 98% in favour. The population of the country was estimated to be around 790,000 at the time of the referendum with only 85,000 registered voters. Voter turnout was 84.3%.<ref>[http://www.electionguide.org/results.php?ID=341 IFES Election Guide]</ref>
