{{Politics of Somalia}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Somalia]] on 25 August 1979. The new constitution replaced the one approved in [[Somali constitutional referendum, 1961|1961]], and introduced a [[one-party state]] with a [[presidential system]] of government. It was approved by 99.78% of voters.<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/so.html Elections in Somalia] African Elections Database</ref>
